{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"A+B+C implemented on PR #66 (commit ec85e4cd5) and verified end-to-end. The original container-RuntimeError fix (commit a5dec5f60) restored the agentic Pass-1 tier, which exposed two latent failures — both fixed: (C) agentic ticket tools read a separate read-only PINNED copy of the ticket store materialized from the 'tickets' ref into <store>/tickets-<sha>/.tickets-tracker/ (new _active_tickets_root contextvar + cfg.tickets_path, mirroring the code-root mechanism; code snapshot untouched/attestation-faithful); (B) read-only ticket contract (comment withheld when reading a pinned snapshot); (A) UsageLimits(tool_calls_limit) backstop so a failing/looping tool can't burn the budget (pydantic-ai #2593). Design validated against pydantic-ai v1.107 idioms (deps-injected pinned root; tool_calls_limit) + peers (OpenAI Agents SDK read-only sandboxes, LangGraph checkpoints). Verified: review-plan on epic 5ca8 now logs 0 'container bin FAILED', 0 'cannot list .tickets-tracker' (was 26), 0 step-budget exhaustions (was 2); container tier runs a real agentic call; verdict PASS (was INDETERMINATE), 21 llm_calls. 291 plan-review/store tests pass."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782611954054661001,"uuid":"860409f5-f6cd-4074-9a51-430bfe6363fc"}